---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
const CONTACT_EMAIL = 'info@worldradiostations.org';
---
<Base
  title="Privacy Policy — World Radio Stations"
  description="How we handle data in the app and on this site. AdMob, AdSense, cookies, GDPR."
>
  <article class="container legal">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="updated">Last updated: May 28, 2026</p>

    <p>
      This policy explains how <strong>World Radio Stations</strong> (the Android app and the
      website, together the “service”) handles information. We respect your privacy and have
      designed the service to collect as little data as possible.
    </p>

    <h2>1. Who controls the data</h2>
    <p>
      The service is developed and maintained by an independent developer (“we”). We have no
      servers that store user data. For questions about this policy, write to
      <a href={`mailto:${CONTACT_EMAIL}`}>{CONTACT_EMAIL}</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>2. Data the service collects</h2>
    <p>
      <strong>We do not store personal data on our servers.</strong> We don’t maintain user
      accounts and don’t require registration.
    </p>
    <h3>In the Android app</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Favorite stations and listen history</strong> are stored only locally on your
        device and are never sent to us.
      </li>
      <li>
        You can delete this information at any time by clearing the app’s data in your device
        settings or by uninstalling it.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <h3>On this site</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Your chosen view, last played station, favorites, history and country</strong>
        are saved in your browser’s <em>localStorage</em>. They never leave your device and
        cannot be read by us or other sites.
      </li>
      <li>
        A <strong>consent cookie</strong> (<code>wrs-consent-v1</code>) is saved if you make a
        choice in the cookie banner, so we don’t ask you again. It contains no personal data.
      </li>
      <li>
        You can clear all of this data from your browser settings (“Clear site data” for this
        site’s domain).
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. Use of the internet</h2>
    <p>The service connects to the internet for the following purposes:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Streaming radio stations</strong> — audio streams come directly from the
        servers of the respective stations. The catalog is retrieved from the public API of
        <a href="https://www.radio-browser.info/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">radio-browser.info</a>.
        When you listen to a station, your IP address may be visible to its operator — as with
        any web streaming.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Ads</strong> — the app shows ads through Google AdMob, and this site plans to
        show ads through Google AdSense (see the next section).
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Fonts</strong> — the site loads Google Fonts from
        <code>fonts.googleapis.com</code>. Google may see your IP address when they load.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>4. Ads (Google AdMob and Google AdSense)</h2>
    <p>
      The app uses <strong>Google AdMob</strong> and the site plans to use
      <strong>Google AdSense</strong> to display ads. These ad networks and their partners may
      set cookies and collect information such as:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>The advertising identifier of the device or browser</li>
      <li>IP address, device type, operating system, browser type</li>
      <li>Coarse geolocation (country/city level)</li>
      <li>Interaction with the ads (impressions, clicks)</li>
      <li>Pages visited on the site</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      The purpose is to show more relevant ads, measure their performance and prevent fraud.
      This data is processed by Google according to:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <a href="https://policies.google.com/technologies/ads" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
          How Google uses information from sites and apps that use its services
        </a>
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="https://policies.google.com/technologies/partner-sites" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
          Policy for partner sites and apps
        </a>
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
          Google Privacy Policy
        </a>
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      Managing personalized ads:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>On Android: <em>Settings → Google → Ads → Opt out of personalized ads</em>.</li>
      <li>In the browser: <a href="https://adssettings.google.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google Ads Settings</a>.</li>
      <li>On the site: you can choose “Necessary only” in the cookie banner.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>5. Cookies on the site</h2>
    <p>The site uses two kinds of cookies and similar technologies:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Technically necessary</strong> — <code>localStorage</code> entries for your
        chosen view, favorites, history, country and cookie choice. Without them the app cannot
        remember your preferences.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Advertising (third party)</strong> — Google AdSense and its partners may set
        cookies to personalize ads. These cookies are set only after your approval in the banner
        or after AdSense is activated.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>6. Your rights under the GDPR</h2>
    <p>If you are a resident of the European Union, you have the right to:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Access your personal data</li>
      <li>Rectification or erasure (the “right to be forgotten”)</li>
      <li>Restrict or object to processing</li>
      <li>Data portability</li>
      <li>Withdraw consent to processing at any time</li>
      <li>Lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority (your local data protection authority)</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      Since we don’t store personal data on our servers, most rights are exercised directly from
      your device — clearing the app’s data on Android, or clearing the site data in your
      browser. For questions about data processed by Google AdMob/AdSense, please contact Google
      through the links above.
    </p>

    <h2>7. Children</h2>
    <p>
      The service is not intended for children under 13, and we do not knowingly collect data
      from children under that age. If you believe we have received such data, please contact
      us so we can delete it.
    </p>

    <h2>8. Security</h2>
    <p>
      The site is served over HTTPS. Since we don’t hold personal data on a server, the main
      privacy risks relate to your device and to third parties (Radio Browser, Google) — we
      recommend reading their policies as well.
    </p>

    <h2>9. Changes to this policy</h2>
    <p>
      We may update this policy from time to time. Significant changes will be reflected with a
      new date at the top of the page. We recommend checking back periodically.
    </p>

    <h2>10. Contact</h2>
    <p>
      For questions about this policy or your data, please write to:
      <br />
      <a href={`mailto:${CONTACT_EMAIL}`}>{CONTACT_EMAIL}</a>
    </p>
  </article>
</Base>
